ins of Babouvism. Themistocles Rodis asks whether morals declined during the Revolution, and Morris Slavin reassesses the effect on the Revolution of the struggle in section Roi de Sicile between monarchists and republicans. Agnes Smith and James Friguglietti examine the assessment of the Revolution by a contemporary observer (Toulongeon) and a twentieth-century historian (Mathiez).  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 4aHistory. 7aHISTORY / Europe / France.2bisacsh1 aFriguglietti, James, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHarkins, James R., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHudson, Ruth Strong, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aIdzerda, Stanley J., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRodis, Themistocles, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSlavin, Morris, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSmith, Agnes M., eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aSmith, Agnes M., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package Pre-2010z978311127416408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Upgrade eBook-Package pre 2010z978311127724040uhttps://doi.org/10.51644/978088920609040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780889206090423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780889206090/original  a978-3-11-127416-4  ACUP Complete eBook-Package Pre-2010b2010  a978-3-11-127724-0  ACUP Upgrade eBook-Package pre 2010b2010  aGBV-deGruyter-alles